{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLibObject","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE12addToggleRef6notify4datayySvSg_SpySo8_GObjectVGSgs5Int32VtXCSg_AGtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addToggleRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This functionality is intended for binding ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" to a proxy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object managed by another memory manager. This is done with two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"paired references: the strong reference added by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"text":" and a reverse reference to the proxy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object which is either a strong reference or weak reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The setup is that when there are no other references to ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only a weak reference is held in the reverse direction from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the proxy object, but when there are other references held to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", a strong reference is held. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"text":" callback is called","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when the reference from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"text":" to the proxy object should be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“toggled” from strong to weak (","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" true) or weak to strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"is_last_ref"},{"text":" false).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since a (normal) reference must be held to the object before"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calling ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the initial state of the reverse","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"link is always strong."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multiple toggle references may be added to the same gobject,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"however if there are multiple toggle references to an object, none"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of them will ever be notified until all but one are removed.  For","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this reason, you should only ever use a toggle reference if there"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is important state in the proxy object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if you unref the object on another thread, then "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" might"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"still be invoked after "},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and the object argument","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"might be a dangling pointer. If the object is destroyed on other threads,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you must take care of that yourself."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" must be released with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef/addToggleRef(notify:data:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"title":"ObjectRef","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/objectprotocol-implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"}}}